This paper discusses the development of computational agents that are "social," which involves the ability to recognize the behaviors of others and make appropriate choices based on social context. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
